Candidates with alternative degrees will also be considered if they have relevant experience
Design, build, and maintain scalable data pipelines and analytics platforms using Python, PySpark, and cloud technologies such as Databricks and AWS

Preferred
Fundamental understanding of semiconductor device physics and VLSI design
Software development skills with clear, maintainable, and efficient coding practices
Command of SQL for data ingestion, transformation, and optimization
Experience with Python and familiarity with Apache Spark and Databricks
Comfortable working with semi-structured/unstructured data (e.g., Excel, SharePoint)
Familiarity with cloud services (AWS, Azure, or GCP) and containerization (Docker, Kubernetes)
Familiarity with semiconductor-specific formats like STDF, ATDF
Experience with Infrastructure-as-Code (e.g., Terraform) and DevOps tooling (CI/CD, monitoring)
Excellent problem-solving abilities, self-motivation, and strong communication skills
